Amanda Khoza, News24 Magistrates court. (Duncan Alfreds, News24) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Durban &ndash; A man allegedly beat his girlfriend to death with a stick at the Yoko Informal Settlement, near Butterworth, Eastern Cape police said on Tuesday.&nbsp;The man, 40, allegedly assaulted the woman, 39, around 04:50 on Monday morning, Captain Jackson Manatha said.&nbsp;"The suspect used a stick to [allegedly] assault the deceased on her upper body," he said.&nbsp;Manatha said the suspect had been charged with murder and the police were still investigating the motive behind the incident. He was expected to appear in the Butterworth Magistrate's Court on Wednesday.&nbsp;24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.